Package: minicom
Version: 2.00.0
Revision: 2
Architecture: powerpc
Recommends: lrzsz
Source: http://www.netsw.org/net/modem/terminal/%n-%v.src.tar.gz
SourceDirectory: %n-%v
Source-MD5: cfae090b087b67ed04e124ab5c658e70
BuildDepends: gettext-dev, gettext-bin, gettext-tools, gcc3.3
Patch: %f.patch
ConfigureParams: --enable-lock-dir=%p/var/run --enable-dfl-port=/dev/tty.modem --mandir='${prefix}/share/man' --infodir='${prefix}/share/info'
CompileScript: <<
 export CC=gcc-3.3; export CXX=g++-3.3; ./configure %c
 make CC=gcc-3.3 CXX=g++-3.3
<<
DocFiles: ABOUT-NLS AUTHORS COPYING ChangeLog INSTALL NEWS README
Description: Serial communication program
DescDetail: <<
Minicom is a serial communication program. It is a Unix clone of the
well-known MS-DOS Telix program. It has ANSI color, a dialing directory,
dial-a-list, and a scripting language.
<<
